http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Workshop-on-protective-ensemble/article13991307.ece

A workshop on ‘next generation protective ensemble’ was organised at the Defence Bio-Engineering and Electro-Medical Laboratory, a constituent laboratory of DRDO, on Friday. Scientist and Director-General (Life Sciences) Manas K. Mandal said, “There is a need for armed forces, technocrats, research and development organisations, and scientists to work under a common platform to bridge the technological gap in order to develop a state-of-the-art personal protective ensemble, which is multifunctional in nature to provide protection from chemical, biological and radioactive fallout dust covering a broad electromagnetic spectrum.” — Staff Reporter